            <fr:title text="Sheaf of ideals generate quasi-closed immersions">Sheaf of ideals generate quasi-closed immersions</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Construction</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/schm-V16H/" title="Locally distributed space" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-V16H/" display-uri="schm-V16H" type="local">locally distributed space</fr:link>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}]]></fr:tex> a sheaf of ideal of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex>. We define the subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ C_{\mathcal {I}} := \{x \in  X\mid 1 \not \in  \mathcal {I}_x\} ]]></fr:tex>
  Equivalently, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  C_{\mathcal {I}}]]></fr:tex> iff the stalk <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathcal {I}/\mathcal {O}_{X})_x]]></fr:tex> of the quotient distributive lattice at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is non-trivial. This is a closed set, since if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0 = 1]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathcal {I}/\mathcal {O}_{X})_x]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0=1]]></fr:tex> in an open neighbourhood of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>. 
</html:p>
            <html:p>
  Now let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i : C_{\mathcal {I}} \hookrightarrow  X]]></fr:tex> be the closed inclusion. From general topos theory, we know the direct image
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ i_* : \mathrm {Sh}(C_{\mathcal {I}}) \to  \mathrm {Sh}(X) ]]></fr:tex>
  is <html:em>fully faithful</html:em>, whose essentially image consists of those sheaves <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {F}_x \cong  1]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in \overline {C_{\mathcal {I}}}]]></fr:tex> (see e.g. <fr:link href="/topl-6LIP/" title="Reflector for closed subtopoi" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-6LIP/" display-uri="topl-6LIP" type="local">Construction <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-6LIP/" display-uri="topl-6LIP" /></fr:link>). This is in particular true for the quotient sheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}/\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex>, since for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in \overline {C_{\mathcal {I}}}]]></fr:tex>, by <fr:link href="/schm-9YD5/" title="Closed quotient commutes with taking stalks" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-9YD5/" display-uri="schm-9YD5" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-9YD5/" display-uri="schm-9YD5" /></fr:link> we have 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ (\mathcal {I}/\mathcal {O}_{X})_x \cong  \mathcal {I}_x/\mathcal {O}_{X,x} ]]></fr:tex>
  and by definition for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  C_{\mathcal {I}}]]></fr:tex>, we know <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}_x/\mathcal {O}_{X,x}]]></fr:tex> is the trivial distributive lattice. Hence, there is an essentially unique sheaf of distributive lattices <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{C_{\mathcal {I}}}]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i_*\mathcal {O}_{C_{\mathcal {I}}} \cong  \mathcal {I}/\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex>. 
</html:p>
            <html:p>
  Furthermore, for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  C_{\mathcal {I}}]]></fr:tex>, the map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i^*\mathcal {O}_{X} \to  \mathcal {O}_{C_{\mathcal {I}}}]]></fr:tex> on stalk over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is given by the quotient 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \mathcal {O}_{X,x} \twoheadrightarrow  \mathcal {I_x}/\mathcal {O}_{X,x} ]]></fr:tex>
  By construction this is a closed quotient of a local distributive lattice where the quotient is non-trivial. Hence, it is a morphism of locally distributed spaces, and we get a quasi-closed immersion
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ C_{\mathcal {I}} \hookrightarrow  X ]]></fr:tex></html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
